Class UserBean

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ami.mse.ucms.security.UserBean

    @Named(value="userBean")
@ViewAccessScoped
public class UserBean
extends Object
implements Serializable
    Contains methods for processing instance of User. There are methods for extracting information for user, save new user, edit existing user and etc.

      • editPageLoad

        public String editPageLoad()
        Called when user-edit page is load. Sets currentUser to be that the user want to edit. Sets variable that show that the currentUser is going to be edit. Makes password and verifyPassword empty. Extract roles for the user if any. Initialize DualListModel.
        Returns:
        redirect to user-edit page

      • onLoadLoggedDetails

        public void onLoadLoggedDetails()
        Called when view-logged-details is loaded. Sets currentUser to be the logged user, if there is logged.

      • save

        public String save()
        Saves instance of User or update one. Check if there is existing user with the same username or EGN and if there is sets message for it. Checks if password and the verifyPassword are equals, it they are not sets message for it. If the verification is complete checks if the user is going to edit existing profile or makes new one. If he make new sets all parameters to the new instance of User and passed to the UserManager. If the user has role "admin" and editing existing sets roles to the instance before pass it to the UserManager. Sets messages for creating new user or editing old.
        Returns:
        refresh the view

      • findAll

        Returns:
        list of Users

      • findUserByEGN

        public String findUserByEGN()

        Returns:
        refresh the page if the user profile if not found or redirect to the user-details page if the profile exists.

      • showDetails

        public void showDetails()
